==English==

===Etymology===
The earliest known use of the term is from the southern cape of [[w:Baja California|Baja California]], as used by the windsurfers and fishermen from the United States. Its earliest use has been placed to 1990, Los Barrilles, BCS, though it may have been in use prior to that time.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|head=[[Baja]] [[midnight|Midnight]]}}

# {{context|US|Baja California}} A time of [[night]] when one is [[tired]] or feels as if it were [[midnight]] before it actually is, usually considered to be between 8pm and 9pm local time.